@BRAND_ID =

### Quick notes
# - Use the Register/Login requests to obtain an access token and paste it into `@ADMIN_TOKEN`.
# - Some endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}` (admin only).

### 1) Health
GET {{BASE_URL}}/health

### 2) Docs (Swagger UI)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/docs

### 3) Register (invalid) - should return 400
POST {{BASE_URL}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "username": "u",
  "password": "123"
}

### 4) Register admin (valid)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin-test+rest@example.com",
  "username": "admintest",
  "password": "StrongPass123!",
  "fullname": "Admin Test",
  "role": "admin"
}

# After successful registration, call Login and copy the `token` value into @ADMIN_TOKEN

### 5) Login admin (get token)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin-test+rest@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!"
}

### 6) Get current user (requires token)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/me
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}

### 7) Create brand (admin) - optional (if API supports)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/brands
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "TestBrand"
}

### 8) Create category (admin) - optional (if API supports)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Laptops"
}

# If your API doesn't have /brands or /categories creation endpoints, set @BRAND_ID and @CATEGORY_ID manually.

### 9) Create item (admin)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/items
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Laptop X",
  "price": 1299.99,
  "amount": 5,
  "category_id": "{{CATEGORY_ID}}",
  "brand_id": "{{BRAND_ID}}",
  "model": "X1000",
  "specs": "16GB RAM, 512GB SSD",
  "warranty": "2 years"
}

### 10) List items (admin)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/items
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}

### 11) Create customer (admin)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "johndoe@example.com",
  "phone": "+36701234567"
}

### 12) Create manual order (admin)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "item_id": "<REPLACE_WITH_ITEM_ID>",
  "customer_id": "<REPLACE_WITH_CUSTOMER_ID>",
  "quantity": 1,
  "status": "completed"
}

### 13) Export orders CSV (admin)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/orders/export?status=all
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}

### 14) Forgot password (initiates reset)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "johndoe@example.com"
}

### 15) Reset password (use token from DB or logs)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "<PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE>",
  "newPassword": "NewStrongPass123!"
}

### 16) Negative: access protected route without token (should return 401)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/me